HEADWORD: Cadilesker
<hw>Ca`di*les"ker</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Ar.
<ets>q⟦amac⟧⟦dsdot⟧⟦imac⟧</ets> judge + <ets>al'sker</ets> the army,
Per. <ets>leshker</ets>.]</ety> <def>A chief judge in the Turkish
empire, so named originally because his jurisdiction extended to the
cases of soldiers, who are now tried only by their own
officers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cadillac</ent>⟦br⟧
